  "niche": {
    "entity_count": 120,
    "description": "Curated contaminant-anchor roster x CDS GCF_000006765.1 ASM676v1 (NCBI, public domain). 20 loci: the central-metabolism backbone (gltA/acnB/icd/sdhA + ATP synthase \u2014 the generalist's broad carbon catabolism) + the Pel/Psl/alginate biofilm EPS machinery (the disinfectant-resistant matrix) + the quorum-sensing (lasR/rhlR/pqsA) and multidrug-efflux (mexB/oprM) + oxidative-defence (katA/sodB) apparatus (the cull-resistance levers). P. aeruginosa PAO1: 6,264,404 bp / 5,570 ORFs; grows in distilled water, largest regulatory-gene set of any genome then sequenced, EPS biofilm resists disinfectants -> defeats the nutrient-starvation + disinfectant barrier. The immigration kernel reads role + trait levers, not specific genes (ADR-019 S0, Mode A contaminant).",
